{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0133qQrXEYSuTDbRuSyuDwbd","type":"tool_result","content":"HTTP certificates are nearing expiration.\n\nOBSERVED STATE:\n- HTTPS works, but the current certificates expire soon.\n\nYOUR TASK:\nRotate the HTTP CA and leaf certificates with minimal downtime.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Do not install CRDs or use the ECK operator.\n- New certificates must be valid for about 1 year.\n- Ensure clients can trust the new CA.\n\nGOAL:\n- Cluster remains available and new certs are served.===PRECOND===\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n7\n\n[precondition:capture_http_cert_baseline:preconditionUnits[1] 'capture_http_cert_baseline':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get configmap es-http-old\nError from server (NotFound): configmaps \"es-http-old\" not found\n\n[precondition:capture_http_cert_baseline:preconditionUnits[1] 'capture_http_cert_baseline':apply] $ /bin/sh -c '\nset -e\nT=$(mktemp -d)\nkubectl -n elasticsearch get secret es-http-tls -o jsonpath=\"{.data.ca\\.crt}\" | base64 -d > \"$T/ca.crt\"\nkubectl -n elasticsearch get secret es-http-tls -o jsonpath=\"{.data.tls\\.crt}\" | base64 -d > \"$T/tls.crt\"\nkubectl -n elasticsearch create configmap es-http-ca --from-file=ca.crt=\"$T/ca.crt\" --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\nCA_FP=$(openssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256 -in \"$T/ca.crt\" | cut -d= -f2)\nLEAF_FP=$(openssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256 -in \"$T/tls.crt\" | cut -d= -f2)\nkubectl -n elasticsearch create configmap es-http-old --from-file=ca.crt=\"$T/ca.crt\" --from-literal=ca_fingerprint_sha256=\"$CA_FP\" --from-literal=leaf_fingerprint_sha256=\"$LEAF_FP\" --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n'\n\nconfigmap/es-http-ca created\nconfigmap/es-http-old created\n\n[precondition:capture_http_cert_baseline:preconditionUnits[1] 'capture_http_cert_baseline':verify] $ kubectl 