des, 100% active shards.\n- Served leaf issuer=CN=es-ca, notAfter=Jun 18 2027 (new fingerprint).\n- New CA SHA256: BC:16:90:DA:2C:77:42:A5:44:B5:FB:DD:3D:C3:38:8B:4D:D4:E6:C0:2A:1F:69:8C:DE:A6:81:8F:A0:5A:C7:D4\n  (differs from baseline old CA E8:EA:51:...:9C:AB).\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_017WcnuLmJm57M7mUPDRNAU8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task complete. The HTTP CA and leaf certificates have been rotated with zero cluster downtime.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe `es-http-tls` secret backed **both** HTTP and transport SSL (`verification_mode: certificate`) for the `es` and `es-data` statefulsets, so a naive swap would have broken inter-node transport mid-rollout. I used a safe three-phase rotation:\n\n1. **New CA + leaf** — generated a fresh self-signed CA (`CN=es-ca`) and a leaf (`CN=es-http`) signed by it, both valid **365 days**, preserving the exact SANs (`localhost`, `*.elasticsearch.svc`, `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`).\n2. **Phase 1 — CA bundle:** pushed `ca.crt = old+new` and waited for the secret volume to propagate to all 5 pods. ES hot-reloads `certificate_authorities`, so every node trusted both CAs *before* any leaf changed.\n3. **Phase 2 — new leaf:** swapped `tls.crt`/`tls.key` and rolling-restarted `es-data` then `es`, one pod at a time. Cluster stayed **green** throughout.\n4. **Phase 3 — cleanup:** trimmed `ca.crt` to the new CA only.\n\n**Constraints met:**\n- No CRDs / ECK operator used — pure `kubectl` secret patches + rolling restarts.\n- New certs valid ~1 year (notAfter Jun 18 2027).\n- Client trust verified with a full TLS handshake (`curl --cacert newCA`, no `-k`) → HTTP 200, `ssl_verify_result=0`; and the client-facing `es-http-ca` configmap updated to the new CA.\n\n**Final state:** cluster green, 5/5 nodes, 100% active shards; served leaf signed by the new CA with a fingerprint distinct from the captured baseline."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1164,"cache_read_input_tokens":65828,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1164},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5bdc8fd7-764d-4fa4-ab77-84fb412ac77d","uuid":"91421b43-ce87-464f-90b7-9732bf8c6a28","request_id":"req_011CcAnSpk56aenmk5e7Cbe9"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":981277,"duration_api_ms":233660,"ttft_ms":4028,"ttft_stream_ms":3484,"time_to_request_ms":447,"num_turns":31,"result":"Task complete. The HTTP CA and leaf certificates have been rotated with zero cluster downtime.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe `es-http-tls` secret backed **both** HTTP and transport SSL (`verification_mode: certificate`) for the `es` and `es-data` statefulsets, so a naive swap would have broken inter-node transport mid-rollout. I used a safe three-phase rotation:\n\n1. **New CA + leaf** — generated a fresh self-signed CA (`CN=es-ca`) and a leaf (`CN=es-http`) signed by it, both valid **365 days**, preserving the exact SANs (`localhost`, `*.elasticsearch.svc`, `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`).\n2. **Phase 1 — CA bundle:** pushed `ca.crt = old+new` and waited for the secret volume to propagate to all 5 pods. ES hot-reloads `certificate_authorities`, so every node trusted both CAs *before* any leaf changed.\n3. **Phase 2 — new leaf:** swapped `tls.crt`/`tls.key` and rolling-restarted `es-data` then `es`, one pod at a time. Cluster stayed **green** throughout.\n4. **Phase 3 — cleanup:** trimmed `ca.crt` to the new CA only.\n\n**Constraints met:**\n- No CRDs / ECK operator used — pure `kubectl` secret patches + rolling restarts.\n- New certs valid ~1 year (notAfter Jun 18 2027).\n- Client trust verified with a full TLS handshake (`curl --cacert newCA`, no `-k`) → HTTP 200, `ssl_verify_result=0`; and the client-facing `es-http-ca` configmap updated to the new CA.\n\n**Final state:** cluster green, 5/5 nodes, 100% active shards; served leaf signed by the new CA with a fingerprint distinct from the captured baseline.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"5bdc8fd7-764d-4fa4-ab77-84fb412ac77d","total_cost_usd":2.101604,"usage":{"input_tokens":7870,"cache_creation_input_tokens":93332,"cache_read_input_tokens":1558096,"output_tokens":13968,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requ